ELIZA:
No. It's from his father.

1168
01:04:55,500 --> 01:04:56,880
HAMILTON:
His father?

1169
01:04:56,880 --> 01:05:00,460
LAURENS:
And when our children tell our story.

1170
01:05:00,460 --> 01:05:02,460
HAMILTON:
Will you read it for me?

1171
01:05:02,460 --> 01:05:08,060
LAURENS:
They'll tell the story of tonight.

1172
01:05:09,220 --> 01:05:11,060
ELIZA:
"On Tuesday the 27th,

1173
01:05:11,060 --> 01:05:17,460
"my son was killed in a gunfight against
British troops retreating from South Carolina.

1174
01:05:18,560 --> 01:05:25,140
"The war was already over. As you know,
John dreamed of emancipating and recruiting

1175
01:05:25,140 --> 01:05:34,560
"3000 men for the first all-black military regiment.
His dream of freedom for these men dies with him."

1176
01:05:35,460 --> 01:05:40,700
LAURENS:
Tomorrow there'll be more of us...

1177
01:05:42,700 --> 01:05:45,460
ELIZA:
Alexander. Are you alright?

1178
01:05:46,380 --> 01:05:48,500
HAMILTON:
I have so much work to do.

1179
01:05:49,220 --> 01:05:51,480
BURR:
After the war I went back to New York

1180
01:05:51,480 --> 01:05:54,280
HAMILTON:
A-After the war I went back to New York

1181
01:05:54,280 --> 01:05:57,020
BURR:
I finished up my studies and I practiced law

1182
01:05:57,020 --> 01:05:59,320
HAMILTON:
I practiced law, Burr worked next door

1183
01:05:59,320 --> 01:06:02,320
BURR:
Even though we started at the very same time

1184
01:06:02,320 --> 01:06:04,700
Alexander Hamilton began to climb

1185
01:06:04,700 --> 01:06:10,580
How to account for his rise to the top?
Maaaaan, the man is non-stop!

1186
01:06:10,580 --> 01:06:13,220
HAMILTON:
Gentlemen of the jury, I'm curious, bear with me

1187
01:06:13,220 --> 01:06:15,260
Are you aware that we're making hist'ry?

1188
01:06:15,260 --> 01:06:18,260
This is the first murder trial
of our brand-new nation

1189
01:06:18,260 --> 01:06:20,720
The liberty behind deliberation--
(Non-stop!)

1190
01:06:20,720 --> 01:06:23,660
I intend to prove beyond a shadow of a doubt
