the work divided evenly among the three men.

1276
01:10:16,400 --> 01:10:20,700
In the end, they wrote eighty-five essays,
in the span of six months.

1277
01:10:21,680 --> 01:10:26,560
John Jay got sick after writing five.
James Madison wrote twenty-nine.

1278
01:10:27,160 --> 01:10:30,240
Hamilton wrote the other fifty-one!

1279
01:10:31,860 --> 01:10:34,200
How do you write like you're
Running out of time?

1280
01:10:34,200 --> 01:10:37,200
Write day and night like you're
Running out of time?

1281
01:10:37,200 --> 01:10:39,540
Ev'ry day you fight like you're
Running out of time

1282
01:10:39,540 --> 01:10:42,540
Like you're running out of time
Are you running out of time?

1283
01:10:42,540 --> 01:10:47,560
How do you write like tomorrow won't arrive?
How do you write like you need it to survive?

1284
01:10:47,560 --> 01:10:52,900
How do you write ev'ry second you're alive?
Ev'ry second you're alive? Ev'ry second you're alive?

1285
01:10:53,760 --> 01:10:56,160
WASHINGTON:
They are asking me to lead

1286
01:10:56,160 --> 01:11:01,180
I am doing the best I can
To get the people that I need

1287
01:11:01,180 --> 01:11:04,600
I'm asking you to be my right hand man
HAMILTON: Treasury or State?

1288
01:11:04,600 --> 01:11:07,120
WASHINGTON: I know it's a lot to ask
HAMILTON: Treasury or State?

1289
01:11:07,120 --> 01:11:08,800
WASHINGTON:
To leave behind the world you know...

1290
01:11:08,800 --> 01:11:11,800
HAMILTON:
Sir, do you want me to run the
Treasury or State department?

1291
01:11:13,060 --> 01:11:13,860
WASHINGTON:
Treasury

1292
01:11:14,500 --> 01:11:15,420
HAMILTON:
Let's go

1293
01:11:17,540 --> 01:11:18,420
ELIZA:
Alexander...

1294
01:11:18,420 --> 01:11:19,780
HAMILTON:
I have to leave

1295
01:11:19,780 --> 01:11:21,020
ELIZA:
Alexander--

1296
01:11:21,020 --> 01:11:26,300
HAMILTON:
Look around, look around at how
lucky we are to be alive right now

1297
01:11:26,300 --> 01:11:27,260
ELIZA:
Helpless...

1298
01:11:27,260 --> 01:11:27,560
HAMILTON:
They are asking me to lead
ELIZA:
Helpless...

1299
01:11:27,560 --> 01:11:29,280
HAMILTON:
They are asking me to lead

1300
01:11:29,280 --> 01:11:31,620
ELIZA:
Look around, isn't this enough?

1301
01:11:31,620 --> 01:11:34,380
ANGELICA: He will never be satisfied
ELIZA: What would be enough

1302
01:11:34,380 --> 01:11:36,580
ANGELICA:
He will never be satisfied

1303
01:11:36,580 --> 01:11:43,060
Satisfied, satisfied
WASHINGTON: History has its eyes on you!

