1311
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I’ve got to be, I’ve gotta be,
I’ve gotta be…

1312
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
In the room!

1313
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What?

1314
01:12:20,640 --> 01:12:22,640
AARON BURR:
1789!

1315
01:12:22,640 --> 01:12:27,640
How does the bastard orphan
Immigrant decorated war vet

1316
01:12:27,640 --> 01:12:31,640
Unite the colonies through more debt?
Fight the other founding fathers til he has to forfeit?

1317
01:12:31,640 --> 01:12:34,640
Have it all, lose it all
You ready for more yet?

1318
01:12:34,640 --> 01:12:39,640
Treasury Secretary. Washington’s the President
Ev’ry American experiment sets a precedent

1319
01:12:39,640 --> 01:12:45,640
Not so fast. Someone came along to resist him
Pissed him off until we had a two-party system

1320
01:12:45,640 --> 01:12:51,640
You haven’t met him yet, you haven’t had the chance
‘cause he’s been kickin’ ass as the ambassador to France

1321
01:12:51,640 --> 01:12:56,640
But someone’s gotta keep the American promise
You simply must meet Thomas. Thomas!

1322
01:13:25,640 --> 01:13:28,640
JEFFERSON:
France is following us to revolution

1323
01:13:28,640 --> 01:13:34,640
There is no more status quo
But the sun comes up and the world still spins

1324
01:13:34,640 --> 01:13:40,640
I helped Lafayette draft a declaration
Then I said, ‘I gotta go

1325
01:13:40,640 --> 01:13:46,640
I gotta be in Monticello.’ Now the work at
Home begins…

1326
01:13:50,640 --> 01:13:56,640
So what’d I miss?
What’d I miss?

1327
01:13:56,640 --> 01:13:59,640
Virginia, my home sweet home,
I wanna give you a kiss

1328
01:14:00,640 --> 01:14:06,640
I’ve been in Paris meeting lots of different ladies...
I guess I basic’lly missed the late eighties...

